<body>
<p>May 2, 2012. <italic>The Scream</italic> by Edvard Munch, the Norwegian expressionist (or symbolist according to others<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="bibr1-1066896912456083">1</xref>,<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="bibr2-1066896912456083">2</xref></sup>) has become the most expensive artwork sold at auction, after it fetched $119.9 million.<sup><xref ref-type="bibr" rid="bibr3-1066896912456083">3</xref></sup></p>
<p>Examination of the umbilical cord (<xref ref-type="fig" rid="fig1-1066896912456083">Figure 1</xref>) can produce a cheaper—if not less depressing—Ersatz aesthetic expression for the everyday pathologist in these moments of worldwide economic distress.</p>
